r642 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 04:34:37 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 3 lines

- Changed requires to reflect the name change of the base class and the addition
  of the PrivilegedEvent class.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r641 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 04:34:02 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 16 lines

- Updated description in the docs header.

- Converted defaults to class constants instead of class variables.

- Aesthetic fixes.

- Added queue name to allow differentiation between multiple running queues.

- Added code to filter out sub-threads that were started by workers from the
  ones monitored by the supervisor.

- Factored out some of the code from the supervisor thread routine to secondary
  methods.

- Fixed shutdown to force-kill stubborn/hung threads.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r640 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 03:33:21 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 3 lines

- Moved the configuration constructor to MUES::Config to decouple this class
  from the configuration implementation a bit.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r639 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 03:31:35 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 55 lines

- Updated documentation in header to reflect recent changes.

- Included new TaintingFunctions mixin. Still needs more integration.

- Converted Version constant construction to more Emacs-friendly code
  (:ruby-mode:).

- Added another EventQueue running under a less-restrictive $SAFE level for
  events which require it.

- Reorganized the constructor

- Removed the per-type objectstores in favor of a single one with a 'Class'
  index.

- Removed accessors for some internal data structures which should not be
  externally visible: users, loginSessions, commandShellFactory.

- Reworked configuration to further decouple the implementation of the
  underlying config mechanism from the subsystem code.

- Removed the last vestiges of the @log handle.

- Moved the setup* methods and a few others into the protected section.

- Uncommented and tested the signal-handling code.

- Reworked the shutdown cycle so that #stop just advises the main thread of the
  shutdown state, and the main thread then does most of the work. The previous
  model had the notifying thread (the EngineShutdownEvent dispatcher) doing most
  of the shutdown work, which caused EventQueue shutdown to do... interesting
  things.

- Added the split-dispatch to handle privileged events to #dispatchEvents.

- Added a #clearSignalHandlers method to allow (semi-graceful?) termination if
  the engine gets stuck midway through shutdown.

- Renamed structures associated with the IO polling loop to 'IO' instead of
  'Listener' to clarify what they're actually doing (eg., listenerThreadRoutine
  becomes ioThreadRoutine, listenerThread becomes ioThread, etc).

- Reordered exception handlers to catch signals before StandardErrors to reflect
  changes to the exception class hierarchy in Ruby.

- Implemented listener cleanup event handler.

- Removed handler for depecated UserSaveEvent (users are now persisted via the
  objectstore, so they don't need explicit saving).

- Removed the last of the LogEvent-style logging.

- Added untainting of class name and env name to LoadEnvironmentEvent
  handler. This allows it to work in $SAFE <= 2.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r638 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 03:09:13 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 9 lines

- Renamed 'commandspath' to 'commandpath' to reflect changes in the DTD.

- Added "configuration constructors", which construct various subsystem objects
  according to configured values.

- Added dependencies for configuration constructors.

- Updated default config to conform to DTD.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r637 | deveiant | 2002-09-12 02:59:49 -0700 (Thu, 12 Sep 2002) | 3 lines

- Moved the Module#implements hack to mues/Object.rb and removed the Object.rb
  require to solve load-order issues.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
