r371 | deveiant | 2002-04-08 23:59:51 -0700 (Mon, 08 Apr 2002) | 27 lines

- Integrated the BaseClass to provide a hook into Ruby's class hierarchy for
  classes which don't have a specific superclass defined.

- Added a bunch of assert methods:

  - hasAttribute? - new method
  - hasClassAttribute? - new method
  - hasOperation? - new method
  - hasClassOperation? - new method
  - includesInterface? - new method

- #removeInterface - new method

- #removeAttribute - new method

- #removeOperation - new method

- Improved the information presented by the #inspect method

- #between? - new method

- Fully-qualified the 'Class' object reference in #classObj to avoid getting
  Metaclass::Class by mistake.

- Added an instance#new method, delegated to the anonclass object to facilitate
  using the metaclass object directly.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r370 | deveiant | 2002-04-08 23:52:39 -0700 (Mon, 08 Apr 2002) | 6 lines

