------------------------------------------------------------------------
r236 | deveiant | 2001-11-01 09:52:07 -0800 (Thu, 01 Nov 2001) | 18 lines

- Updated documentation

- Fixed select loop bug. Writable handle now is only select()ed when there's
  something in the write buffer.

- Added SelectTimeout class variable

- Added write(), _sendShutdownMessage() methods

- Abstracted the input handling mechanism from the IO loop to facilitate
  subclasses handling their own input without needing to re-implement the IO
  loop.

- Separated maintenance of the input buffer from parsing of it, again to allow
  subclasses to override either one separately.

- Added a windowSize attribute and accessor

------------------------------------------------------------------------
