Initial release.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r205 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:30:39 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 10 lines

- Added a remoteHost attribute with read-only accessor to hold the remote host
  associated with the socket.

- Removed socket() accessor, as the socket should be private to the filter
  object.

- Added a flushing syswrite() to the shutdown cycle so that messages appended
  immediately before shutdown (eg., reconnect messages and the like) will have a
  chance of being sent.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r204 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:27:49 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 2 lines

- Added user, role, and env attributes, along with read-only accessors for them.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r203 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:25:42 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 5 lines

- Changed default sort order to 650 from 200.

- Added class variable 'MacroPrefix' to defined the default sigil to invoke the
  macro filter.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r202 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:24:31 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 6 lines

- Renamed isFinished() to isFinished?(), with an alias back to isFinished(),
  which is now deprecated, and will probably be removed in the next couple of
  versions.

- Added a to_s() method.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r201 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:22:29 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 15 lines

- Added code to handle IOEventFilters as the return value of commands.

- Changed explicit prompt to an OutputPromptEvent.

- Added a UserSaveEvent to the return value of the quit command.

- Renamed the 'play' command to 'connect' with a 'play' synonym, and fixed a
  couple of bugs in its invoke().

- Added a 'roles' command to list available roles.

- Corrected all of the invoke() method signatures in the documentation

- Added a 'disconnect' command.

