r197 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:01:13 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 2 lines

- Added some debugging to the user save code.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r196 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 06:00:49 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 10 lines

- Renamed remoteIp() to remoteHost().

- Removed the characters array from the dbInfo hash. Environments should really
  keep track of their own Character => User map if they need one.

- Removed registration of interest in TickEvents, as they weren't being used for
  anything, and so were just a useless dispatch.

- Fixed the handling of reconnect display messages.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r195 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:56:54 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 3 lines

- Removed the indent from the string generated by to_s(), as it was not very
  Principle of Least Surprise. =:)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r194 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:54:45 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 5 lines

- Added object finalizer-generation class method to facilitate tracking down
  leaked objects.

- Added thread-desc to the output of debugMsg() in the Debuggable mixin.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r193 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:52:22 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 6 lines

- Added read-only accessors for remoteHost, loginAttemptCount, and maxTries.

- Fixed some of the circular references that are causing LoginSession objects to
  leak after login. Still haven't tracked them all down, but I eliminated most
  of 'em from the authSuccessCallback().

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r192 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:50:17 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 8 lines

- Added a new method findFiltersOfType() to complement removeFiltersOfType().

- Added code to skip the handle{Input,Output}Events() calls on "finished"
  filters going into the _filter{Input,Output}Events() methods. This was added
  to allow preceeding filters to finish ones later in the chain of
  responsibility (eg., the CommandShell can disconnect a ParticipantProxy from a
  /disconn command, etc.).

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r191 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:44:50 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 2 lines

- Defined two new exceptions: CommandError and MacroError

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r190 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:43:59 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 6 lines

- Resolved some potential scoping issues inside the worker threads' event
  loop. Since the consequences events were in the same scope as the
  (potentially) blocking dequeue() call, it was possible that the consequence
  events would still be referred to by the blocked child. Fixed by wrapping the
  call to the handler in a begin .. end block.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r189 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:41:22 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 2 lines

- Added loader code for loading environment classes on request.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r188 | deveiant | 2001-09-26 05:40:32 -0700 (Wed, 26 Sep 2001) | 6 lines

- Added remote host and lastLogin time setting to the UserLoginEvent handler

- Bug: LoginSessions weren't being removed from the loginSessions array: fixed.

- Added GarbageCollectionEvent handler

------------------------------------------------------------------------
