r91 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:14:36 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 3 lines

- Fixed call to the superclass's constructor. Was passing an array rather than a
  splat-array.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r90 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:13:01 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 6 lines

- Modified to use the observer pattern to reflect changes in the design of the
  IOEventStream class. Filters now notify the stream/s they belong to (who are
  observers of their filters) instead of constantly polling for pending events.

- Added start() and stop() methods.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r89 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:10:59 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 3 lines

- Simplified and made to use blocking IO, as $stdout has a way of always being
  writable. =:)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r88 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:10:02 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 3 lines

- Moved the initial prompt output event generation to the start() method so it
  doesn't get queued before it has a stream to send it.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r87 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:09:04 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 3 lines

- Made the type- and response-checking functions create more useful exception
  messages.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r86 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 19:08:14 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 7 lines

- Changed the whole IO subsystem to use signalling for notification of pending
  IO events. This eliminates the need to constantly poll the filters, reducing
  the load considerably.

- Added start() and stop() methods to the interface for filters to notify them
  when a stream adds and removes them.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
