r63 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 05:04:50 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

- Added function registerHandlerForEvents()

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r62 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:47:58 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 15 lines

- Converted Mutexen to Syncs to support shared locks

- Changed name of _doStreamThreadRoutine() to _streamThreadRoutine()

- Fully-qualified types in type-checking calls

- Changed the way addEvents() does event dispatching so that it doesn't call a
  method for each event.

- Cleaned up shutdown code

- Added pause() and unpause() methods

- Synchronized filter access so that a removed filter doesn't get handed events.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r61 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:41:35 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

- Added require of console output filter class.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r60 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:40:56 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

- Modified to use e2mmap for exception class definitions

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r59 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:40:20 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 3 lines

- Moved event classes into collections of related events in modules under
  mues/events/.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r58 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:39:12 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 19 lines

- Redesigned internals (same interface, though) as the result of studying other
  implementations.

- The start() method now waits for the supervisor to get ready before returning
  to avoid the problem of events being enqueued (and some unsupervised threads
  being signalled before the supervisor enters its throttle loop.

- Added two-phase startup and shutdown to avoid losing events

- Supervisor's throttle loop now runs until there are no more events, even if
  the shutdown flag is set. This will allow critical events to be processed at
  server shutdown.

- Changed the name of the _doWork() method to _workerThreadRoutine().

- Added infinite recursion trap to _dispatchEvent()

- Turned on workers' abort_on_exception flags.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r57 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:29:07 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 21 lines

- Changed the Mutexen into Syncs to support shared locks

- Made the listener socket private to the listener thread to avoid locking
  issues when reloading, and serialized listener thread creation.

- Fully-qualified type checks

- Hacked up login code to support new LoginSession object

- Made modifications necessary to allow event queue to process critical events
  before shutdown.

- Moved the registerHandlerForEvents method into the MUES namespace as a
  function global to the MUES::Object class.

- Rewrote the ReloadEvent handler to deal with the change to listener
  socket/thread.

- Cleaned up event handling so resultant events are dispatched in the result
  cycle and not immediately.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r56 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:19:34 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 7 lines

- Flush STDERR with each debugging message

- Accept arguments (which get .to_i'ed) of Numeric and String types instead of
  Fixnums for debug levels

- Clarified the error for a unknown debugging level type.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r55 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:16:46 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

- Added 'public' declaration to public method sections.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r54 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:15:07 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

- Turned on debugging in the engine before startup.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r53 | deveiant | 2001-05-14 04:11:35 -0700 (Mon, 14 May 2001) | 2 lines

Initial release

